46. Lu hac est pura Oratim ‘ In this play the attraction is its purity of style,' i. e. not its action. Ambiuius is contrasting the bustling‚ stirring plays in which he has often acted with this quiet (stataria) and more refined drama, where the beauty of style and language is the main feature. For this meaning of oratio, vid. Phorm. prol. 5, Fabalas...tenai esse oratione. Cf. also Cic. Orat. ii. 13, res oratione illustrantur, i.e. put in a clear light by the beauty of the style.
